            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "The **Contoso Electronics Whistleblower Policy** is designed to ensure a safe and transparent working environment. It encourages employees, contractors, and third parties to report any unethical or illegal activities witnessed within the organization. \n\n### Key Elements of the Policy:\n\n1. **Definition**: A whistleblower is an individual reporting unethical, illegal, or non-compliant activities with company policy.\n   \n2. **Reporting Procedures**:\n   - Contact the Human Resources Department.\n   - Send an email to the Compliance Officer at **compliance@contoso.com**.\n   - Call the Compliance Hotline at **1-800-555-1212**.\n   - Reports can be made anonymously via the hotline.\n\n3. **Details to Provide**:\n   - Time and date of the incident.\n   - Identification of parties involved.\n   - Description of the incident.\n   - Supporting evidence.\n\n4. **Confidentiality**:\n   - The whistleblower's identity will be kept confidential as per legal requirements.\n   \n5. **Prohibition of Retaliation**:\n   - Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited and is subject to disciplinary actions, including termination.\n\n6. **Investigation**:\n   - Reported incidents will be promptly and thoroughly investigated.\n\nThis policy reflects Contoso Electronics' commitment to ethical practices and maintaining a secure and trustworthy work environment.",
